comments.body:
Why would you put a picture of a woman in the background of the logo?

Great, now that I've complained about someone else's submission I have to make my own.

Perhaps a little too simple, but how about something along the lines of http://localhost:43110/1EGjFGE7AJx1ZkBG3C7QmGLBJGGXFmbR1F/zeromedia.svg . The base graphic is in the public domain, source (where you can see how pathetically little modification I've made) is https://pixabay.com/en/megaphone-shouting-voice-loud-man-150254/ .

I was trying to think of a generic symbol for "media", and the printing press and the megaphone are the two main things that come to mind. Maybe a printing press would be better, especially since they have the big pulleys that can be made into zeroes :)

I2P has received very little attention from the security community, and when they do pay attention to it they find huge security holes. Tor, while it has known flaws, gets a LOT of attention, and the network is much larger. I'm sticking with Tor.

Plus, JVM. No.
I'm not willing to entrust my data to someone else.
